main event: On September 9, 1966, a civilian observer reported an unidentified object in Franklin Springs, New York, which appeared to be a large, silvery tank-like object that remained motionless for some time before ascending rapidly.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 8-10 minutes but did not appear to move during that time,The observer noted the object's behavior resembling that of a tank,There were no other aircraft reported in the area by the local airport,The absence of photos or physical evidence led to the conclusion that the object was unidentified,Some witnesses noted electrical disturbances accompanying the luminosity of the object.
witness description: A civilian observer who described the object as oblong and glowing.
